ties across Europe. The vast majority of Roma experience high levels of exclusion from the labour market and from social networks in society. This book maps out how the implementation of a new 'Social Europe' can offer innovative solutions to these intransigent dilemmas. This insightful and accessible text is vital reading for the policymaker, practitioner, academic and activist.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aRomaniesxEmploymentzEurope. 0aRomaniesxSocial conditionszEurope. 0aRomaniesxSocializationzEurope. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh1 aCemlyn, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaróczi, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerkovics, Roland, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFranz, Romeo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGalbraith, James K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKóczé, Angéla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMatache, Margareta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRorke, Bernard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRostas, Katalin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRyder, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRyder, Andrew, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSetét, Jenő, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSzilvasi, Marek, econtributor.4ctb4https: